PeriodEnum: The enumerated values to specify the period, e.g. day, week.

description: The enumerated values to specify a time period containing the additional
T: Term. The period commencing on the effective date and ending on the termination date. The T period always appears in association with periodMultiplier = 1, and the notation is intended for use in contexts where the interval thus qualified (e.g. accrual period, payment period, reset period, ...) spans the entire term of the trade.

PeriodTimeEnum: The enumeration values to specify a time period containing additional values such as Term.
TimeUnitEnum: The enumeration values to qualify the allowed units of time.
